    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on exploiting favorable matchups against higher xERA starters, led by our premier speed-power combination in **Trea Turner** (81.27) and **Kyle Schwarber** (79.42). Both are poised for high-ceiling performances against Martin P\u00e9rez; the projected 4.78 xERA provides the soft landing needed for **Trea Turner** to utilize his elite sprint speed, while **Kyle Schwarber** benefits from a strong lineup position and superior contact metrics. Similarly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.79) remains a priority start; despite a lower lineup placement, the combination of wind blowing out and a 4.52 xERA matchup elevates his fantasy utility significantly. **Hyeseong Kim** (70.16) rounds out our top-tier plays, as the combination of park factors and the +17% SP skill adjustment creates a compelling case for him to deliver production despite hitting in the lower third of the order.\n\nWhile the core is strong, we continue to monitor the marginal starts in our C/MI slots. **Dillon Dingler** (55.38) edges out **Gary Sanchez** (49.75) due to a favorable dynamic platoon advantage, though both are operating under high-risk conditions regarding their respective opposing pitchers. The tightest decision on the bench involved **Josh Smith** (38.06), who nearly cracked the lineup based on potential platoon splits against right-handed pitching. Ultimately, the optimizer prioritized the consistent volume of **Caleb Durbin** (51.20) and the specific speed-based defensive upside of **Victor Scott II** (47.57). We are holding **Christian Yelich** on the IL and continue to monitor **Zac Veen** in the minors, while **Colt Keith** remains inactive. We proceed with caution regarding the pending lineups for **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Chase Meidroth**; any late-breaking shifts to lower order spots could further compress the scoring efficiency of these fringe starters.",
